7 10a2.3 2.3 0 0 0 4-1 2.3 2.3 0 0 0-.8-2.2z"></path></defs><use fill-rule="evenodd" xlink:href="#a"></use></svg></button></div></header></div><div class="css-1vcjrad"><aside class="css-r3w5ih"><div data-empty="true" class="css-1y709x9"><div class="css-1hjaa0k"><span class="css-zya54r"></span></div><div id="dlb1__slot" data-ad="true" class="css-16nrrds"></div></div></aside></div><aside class="css-pdceuf"><div class="css-iwb3cn"><button class="icon-hl-close-thick css-1nw70vr"></button><div data-empty="true" class="css-lzra3c"><div class="css-1hjaa0k"><span class="css-zya54r"></span></div><div id="mlb1__slot" data-ad="true" class="css-zutda9"></div></div></div></aside><div class="css-stl7tm"><div data-article-body="true" class="css-13sft9o"><div class="css-z468a2"><h1>How can these popular foods benefit our health?</h1><section class="css-12k7ogr"><div class="css-4nmqvw"><div class="css-12r7hj0">Medically reviewed by <a class="css-0 css-1g08k51" href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/reviewers">Natalie Olsen, RD, LD, ACSM EP-C</a> on September 1, 2017<!-- --> <!-- --> — <!-- -->Written by <!-- -->Joseph Nordqvist</div></div></section><div style="position:relative"><article class="article-body css-18qxptj undefined"><p class="css-dmtxcr">Though the field of medicine continues to advance and branch out in many ways, nutritionists and health experts continue to praise the benefits of certain foods. In fact, eating healthfully has been shown to reduce the risk of obesity, cardiovascular illnesses, and even certain types of cancer.</p><p> However, understanding which foods to eat for specific benefits can sometimes be difficult, which is why <em>Medical News Today</em> previously supplied a list of the <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/245259.php" class="content-link">top 10 healthy foods</a>. </p><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><picture class="css-16pk1is"><source srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/popular-healthy-foods-laid-out-on-white-background.jpg?w=1575 750w" media="(min-width: 1190px)"/><source srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/popular-healthy-foods-laid-out-on-white-background.jpg?w=1575 750w" media="(min-width: 990px)"/><source srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/popular-healthy-foods-laid-out-on-white-background.jpg?w=1845 879w" media="(min-width: 768px)"/><img src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/popular-healthy-foods-laid-out-on-white-background.jpg?w=1155" alt="popular healthy foods laid out on white background" class="css-iq3uei"/></picture></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fpopular-healthy-foods-laid-out-on-white-background.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/popular-healthy-foods-laid-out-on-white-background.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p> Now, <em>MNT</em> specifies the health benefits of a much wider range of foods.</p><div class="css-umsscj"><aside class="css-0"><div><div data-empty="true" class="css-10gx9pb"><div class="css-1hjaa0k"><span class="css-zya54r"></span></div><div id="inline0__slot" data-ad="true" class="css-12zon3z"></div></div></div></aside></div><p>We provide a cornucopia of delicious and nutritious options for individuals who wish to boost their health by eating healthfully. </p><p>Below is a list of foods along with information regarding their potential health benefits. </p><p> Note that this article contains summaries and you should click through to read individual articles containing the full list of possible health benefits.</p><div class="css-1cg0byz"><aside class="css-0"><div><div data-empty="true" class="css-az6x7v"><div class="css-1hjaa0k"><span class="css-zya54r"></span></div><div id="inline1__slot" data-ad="true" class="css-eykv1o"></div></div></div></aside></div><hr/><h2>Almonds</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Almonds" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-almonds.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-almonds.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-almonds.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-almonds.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-almonds.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-almonds.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Almonds are a rich source of <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/195878.php" title="Vitamins: What are they and what do they do?" class="keywords content-link">vitamin</a> E, <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/288165.php" title="Health benefits and risks of copper" class="keywords content-link">copper</a>, <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/286839.php" title="Why do we need magnesium?" class="keywords content-link">magnesium</a>, good quality protein, and healthy unsaturated fatty acids.</p><div id="hl-incontent-video-ad" class="css-1sxbpyw"></div><div id="div-gpt-ad-out-of-page" class="css-1h5aco8"></div><p>Studies have revealed that almonds can potentially help <hl-trusted-source source="PubMed Central" rationale="Highly respected database from the National Institutes of Health"><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12221048" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">prevent cardiovascular diseases</a></hl-trusted-source>, cut the risk of <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/info/cancer-oncology/" title="What is Cancer?" class="keywords content-link">cancer</a>, and help <a href="http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMoa1307352" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">prolong life</a>.</p><div class="css-umsscj"><aside class="css-0"><div><div data-empty="true" class="css-10gx9pb"><div class="css-1hjaa0k"><span class="css-zya54r"></span></div><div id="inline2__slot" data-ad="true" class="css-12zon3z"></div></div></div></aside></div><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/269468.php" class="content-link">Read more about almonds.</a></p><div data-empty="true" class="css-1ivv8yj"><div class="css-1hjaa0k"><span class="css-zya54r"></span></div><div id="ina" data-ad="true" class="css-bviy42"></div></div><hr/><h2>Apples</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Apple and apple slices" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-apples.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-apples.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-apples.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-apples.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-apples.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-apples.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Apples are sometimes called "nutritional powerhouses" because of their impressive nutritional profile.</p><p>Apples contain about 14 percent of our daily needs of Vitamin C (a powerful natural <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/301506.php" title="How can antioxidants benefit our health?" class="keywords content-link">antioxidant</a>), B-complex vitamins, dietary fiber, phytonutrients (which help protect the body from the detrimental effects of free radicals), and minerals such as <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/248958.php" title="Calcium: Health benefits, foods, and deficiency" class="keywords content-link">calcium</a> and <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/287212.php" title="Everything you need to know about potassium" class="keywords content-link">potassium</a>.</p><p>Studies have revealed that eating apples can potentially help <a href="http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1750-3841.2007.00632.x/full" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">prevent dementia</a> and reduce the <hl-trusted-source source="PubMed Central" rationale="Highly respected database from the National Institutes of Health"><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10822289" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">risk of stroke</a></hl-trusted-source> and <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/info/diabetes/" title="What is Diabetes?" class="keywords content-link">diabetes</a><b>.</b></p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/267290.php" class="content-link">Read more about apples.</a></p><div class="css-umsscj"><aside class="css-0"><div><div data-empty="true" class="css-10gx9pb"><div class="css-1hjaa0k"><span class="css-zya54r"></span></div><div id="inline3__slot" data-ad="true" class="css-12zon3z"></div></div></div></aside></div><hr/><h2>Arugula</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="arugula" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/arugula.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/arugula.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/arugula.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/arugula.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Farugula.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/arugula.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Along with other leafy greens, arugula contains very high nitrate levels (more than 250 milligrams per 100 grams). High intakes of dietary nitrate have been shown to lower <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270644.php" title="What is a normal blood pressure?" class="keywords content-link">blood pressure</a>, reduce the amount of oxygen needed during exercise, and enhance athletic performance.</p><p>The potential health benefits of arugula include lowering the risk of cancer, preventing <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/155646.php" title="What to know about osteoporosis" class="keywords content-link">osteoporosis</a>, and improving muscle oxygenation during exercise.</p><div class="swoopContainer"><div id="swoopAd"></div></div><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/282769.php" class="content-link">Read more about arugula.</a></p><div class="css-1cg0byz"><aside class="css-0"><div><div data-empty="true" class="css-az6x7v"><div class="css-1hjaa0k"><span class="css-zya54r"></span></div><div id="inline4__slot" data-ad="true" class="css-eykv1o"></div></div></div></aside></div><hr/><h2>Asparagus</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Asparagus" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-asparagus.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-asparagus.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-asparagus.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-asparagus.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-asparagus.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-asparagus.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Asparagus is very rich in dietary fiber and contains high levels of vitamin B6, calcium, zinc, and magnesium.</p><p>The potential health benefits of asparagus include: reducing the risk of diabetes, preventing <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/154193.php" title="How do you get kidney stones?" class="keywords content-link">kidney stones</a>, and lowering the risk of neural tube defects in babies.</p><div class="css-umsscj"><aside class="css-0"><div><div data-empty="true" class="css-10gx9pb"><div class="css-1hjaa0k"><span class="css-zya54r"></span></div><div id="inline5__slot" data-ad="true" class="css-12zon3z"></div></div></div></aside></div><p>Asparagus is also a natural diuretic, which can help with fluid balance in the body and influence blood pressure and <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/159111.php" title="Everything you need to know about edema" class="keywords content-link">edema</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270805.php" class="content-link">Read more about asparagus.</a></p><hr/><h2>Bananas</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Bananas" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-bananas.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-bananas.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-bananas.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-bananas.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-bananas.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-bananas.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/271157.php" title="Benefits and health risks of bananas" class="keywords content-link">Bananas</a> are naturally free of fat, <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/9152.php" title="What causes high cholesterol?" class="keywords content-link">cholesterol</a>, and sodium, and very rich in potassium.</p><p>The potential health benefits of bananas include: lowering blood pressure, reducing the risk of developing <a href="http://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/142595.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="content-link">childhood leukemia</a>, and supporting heart health.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/271157.php" class="content-link">Read more about bananas.</a></p><div class="css-umsscj"><aside class="css-0"><div><div data-empty="true" class="css-10gx9pb"><div class="css-1hjaa0k"><span class="css-zya54r"></span></div><div id="inline6__slot" data-ad="true" class="css-12zon3z"></div></div></div></aside></div><hr/><h2>Basil</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Basil leaves" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-basil.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-basil.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-basil.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-basil.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-basil.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-basil.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Basil is rich in vitamin A, vitamin K, vitamin C, magnesium, iron, potassium, and calcium.</p><p>Studies have revealed that basil can potentially <a href="http://ijpp.com/IJPP archives/2005_49_2/125-131.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">reduce inflammation and swelling</a>, prevent the harmful <a href="http://www.phytojournal.com/archives/?year=2013&vol=2&issue=2&part=B&ArticleId=152" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">effects of aging</a>, and may be useful in treating <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/7621.php" title="What are the causes and types of arthritis?" class="keywords content-link">arthritis</a> and <a href="http://www.pnas.org/content/105/26/9099.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">inflammatory bowel diseases</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266425.php" class="content-link">Read more about basil.</a></p><hr/><h2>Beetroot</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Beetroot" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/beetroot.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/beetroot.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/beetroot.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/beetroot.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fbeetroot.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/beetroot.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Beetroot, also known simply as the beet, has been gaining in popularity as a new super food due to recent studies claiming that beets and beetroot juice can improve athletic performance, lower blood pressure and increase blood flow.</p><p>This is partly due to its high content of nitrates, which <a href="http://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2125.2012.04420.x" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">increase nitric oxide</a> in the body and play a substantial role in heart and vascular health.</p><p>Beetroot is a rich source of <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/287677.php" title="Why is folate good for you?" class="keywords content-link">folate</a> and manganese, and also contains thiamine, riboflavin, vitamin B-6, pantothenic acid, choline, betaine, magnesium, phosphorus, potassium, zinc, copper, and <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/287842.php" title="Selenium: What it does and how much you need" class="keywords content-link">selenium</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/277432.php" class="content-link">Read more about beetroot.</a></p><hr/><h2>Bok choy</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="bok choy" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/bok-choy.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/bok-choy.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/bok-choy.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/bok-choy.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fbok-choy.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/bok-choy.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Bok choy belongs to the cruciferous vegetable family, which also includes <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270435.php" title="What are the health benefits of kale?" class="keywords content-link">kale</a>, broccoli, cauliflower, Brussels sprouts, cabbage, collard greens, rutabaga, and turnips.</p><p>These <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/160774.php" title="Nutrition: What is it and why is it important?" class="keywords content-link">nutrition</a> powerhouses supply loads of nutrients for little <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/245588.php" title="How many calories should I eat a day?" class="keywords content-link">calories</a>. If you are trying to eat healthier, cruciferous vegetables like bok choy should be at the very top of your grocery list.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/280948.php" class="content-link">Read more about bok choy.</a></p><hr/><h2>Broccoli</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Ripe broccoli" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-broccoli.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-broccoli.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-broccoli.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-broccoli.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-broccoli.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-broccoli.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Broccoli contains high levels of fiber (both soluble and insoluble) and is a rich source of vitamin C.</p><p>In addition, broccoli is rich in vitamin A, iron, vitamin K, B-complex vitamins, zinc, phosphorus, and phytonutrients.</p><p>Studies have found that broccoli can potentially help <a href="http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/art.38133/full" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">prevent osteoarthritis</a>, protect skin against the <a href="http://www.hopkinsmedicine.org/news/media/releases/Broccoli_SproutDerived_Extract_Protects_Against_Ultraviolet_Radiation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">effects of UV light</a>, reverse <a href="http://diabetes.diabetesjournals.org/content/57/10/2809.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">diabetes heart damage</a>, and reduce <hl-trusted-source source="Journal of Nutrition" rationale="Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal"><a href="https://academic.oup.com/jnci/article/91/7/605/2543972/Fruit-and-Vegetable-Intake-and-Incidence-of" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">bladder cancer risk</a></hl-trusted-source>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266765.php" class="content-link">Read more about broccoli.</a></p><hr/><h2>Cantaloupe</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Cantaloupe" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cantaloupe.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cantaloupe.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cantaloupe.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cantaloupe.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fcantaloupe.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cantaloupe.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Cantaloupes are also commonly known as muskmelons, mush melons, rock melons, and Persian melons. They are a member of the botanical family Cucurbitaceae, along with honeydew and watermelons.</p><p>Cantaloupe contains an abundance of antioxidants, including choline, zeaxanthin, and <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/252758.php" title="All you need to know about beta carotene" class="keywords content-link">beta-carotene</a>, all of which protect against a range of diseases and conditions from the common cold to cancer.</p><p>Potential health benefits of cantaloupe include lowering risk of developing <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/info/asthma/" title="What is Asthma?" class="keywords content-link">asthma</a>, managing blood pressure, aiding digestion, keeping hydrated, and reducing <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/248423.php" title="Everything you need to know about inflammation" class="keywords content-link">inflammation</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/279176.php" class="content-link">Read more about cantaloupe.</a></p><hr/><h2>Carrots</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Carrots" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-carrots.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-carrots.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-carrots.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-carrots.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-carrots.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-carrots.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Carrots are a great source of vitamin A. They provide 210 percent of an average adult's needs for the day.</p><p>The potential health benefits of carrots include: <hl-trusted-source source="PubMed Central" rationale="Highly respected database from the National Institutes of Health"><a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/3818153" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">preventing lung cancer</a></hl-trusted-source>, destroying <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/142595.php" title="What to know about leukemia" class="keywords content-link">leukemia</a> cells and <a href="http://online.liebertpub.com/doi/abs/10.1089/jmf.2010.0284" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">inhibiting their progression</a>, and helping to restore vision.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270191.php" class="content-link">Read more about carrots.</a></p><hr/><h2>Cauliflower</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="cauliflower" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cauliflower.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cauliflower.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cauliflower.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cauliflower.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fcauliflower.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cauliflower.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Cauliflowers are a member of the brassica family, more commonly known as cruciferous vegetables.</p><p>They contain antioxidants and phytonutrients that can protect against cancer.</p><p>They also contain fiber that helps with satiety, weight loss, and a healthy digestive tract, choline that is essential for learning and memory, as well as many other important nutrients.</p><p>The potential health benefits of cauliflower include preventing mutations and reducing <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/145855.php" title="Why stress happens and how to manage it" class="keywords content-link">stress</a> from free radicals, preventing <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/150322.php" title="What to know about constipation" class="keywords content-link">constipation</a>, and helping memory.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/282844.php" class="content-link">Read more about cauliflower.</a></p><hr/><h2>Celery</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Celery" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-celery.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-celery.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-celery.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-celery.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-celery.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-celery.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Celery is a very rich source of antioxidants, electrolytes, and vitamin K. Also, thanks to its high water content, it can help rehydrate.</p><p>The potential health benefits of celery include: lowering blood pressure, preventing cancer, and soothing joint pain.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270678.php" class="content-link">Read more about celery.</a></p><hr/><h2>Chickpeas</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="chickpeas" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/chickpeas.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/chickpeas.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/chickpeas.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/chickpeas.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fchickpeas.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/chickpeas.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><span class="css-zya54r"></span><p>Originally cultivated in the Mediterranean and the Middle East, chickpeas, also known as garbanzo beans, have spread their culinary influence throughout the world.</p><p>The potential health benefits of chickpeas include improved glucose levels, lipids, and <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/info/diabetes/whatisinsulin.php" title="What is insulin?" class="keywords content-link">insulin</a> levels for diabetes, maintaining bone strength and heart health.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/280244.php" class="content-link">Read more about chickpeas.</a></p><hr/><h2>Chives</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Bunch of chives" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/bunch-of-chives.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/bunch-of-chives.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/bunch-of-chives.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/bunch-of-chives.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fbunch-of-chives.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/bunch-of-chives.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275009.php" title="Health benefits of chives" class="keywords content-link">Chives</a> are a nutrient-dense food, meaning that while they are low in calories, they are high in beneficial nutrients like vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants.</p><p>The potential health benefits of chives include potential beneficial and preventative effects against cancer, <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/150086.php" title="What's to know about prostate cancer?" class="keywords content-link">prostate cancer</a>, esophageal and <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/257341.php" title="What to know about stomach cancer" class="keywords content-link">stomach cancer</a>, and positive effects on sleep and mood.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275009.php" class="content-link">Read more about chives.</a></p><hr/><h2>Chocolate</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Chocolate" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-chocolate.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-chocolate.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-chocolate.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-chocolate.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-chocolate.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-chocolate.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Chocolate is rich in antioxidants. Despite its bad reputation for causing weight gain, there are a number of health benefits associated with its consumption (particularly dark chocolate).</p><p>The potential benefits of eating chocolate include: lowering cholesterol levels, preventing cognitive decline, and reducing the risk of cardiovascular problems.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270272.php" class="content-link">Read more about chocolate.</a></p><hr/><h2>Cilantro</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Cilantro" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cilantro.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cilantro.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cilantro.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cilantro.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fcilantro.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cilantro.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Known as coriander in the United Kingdom, cilantro comes from the plant <em>Coriandrum sativum</em>. In the United States, the leaves of the plant are referred to as cilantro (the Spanish translation), and the seeds are referred to as coriander.</p><p>Many studies have suggested that increasing consumption of plant foods like cilantro decreases the risk of <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/info/obesity/how-much-should-i-weigh.php" title="How Much Should I Weigh?" class="keywords content-link">obesity</a>, overall mortality, diabetes, and <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/237191.php" title="Everything you need to know about heart disease" class="keywords content-link">heart disease</a> while promoting a healthy skin and hair, increased energy, and overall lower weight.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/277627.php" class="content-link">Read more about cilantro.</a></p><hr/><h2>Cinnamon</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Cinnamon sticks" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-cinnamon.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-cinnamon.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-cinnamon.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-cinnamon.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-cinnamon.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-cinnamon.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Studies have found that <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266069.php" title="What are the health benefits of cinnamon?" class="keywords content-link">cinnamon</a> can potentially be effective <a href="https://search.proquest.com/openview/4ccae43b4086ca488297d37a9e622c3a/1?pq-origsite=gscholar&cbl=37533" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">against HIV</a>, improve glucose and lipid levels in patients <a href="http://care.diabetesjournals.org/content/26/12/3215.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">with type 2 diabetes</a>, help <hl-trusted-source source="PloS One" rationale="Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal"><a href="http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0016564" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">prevent Alzheimer's disease</a></hl-trusted-source>, and stop the destructive <hl-trusted-source source="PubMed Central" rationale="Highly respected database from the National Institutes of Health"><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4568834/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">process of multiple sclerosis</a></hl-trusted-source> (MS).</p><p>In addition, researchers at <a href="http://jn.nutrition.org/content/141/8/1451.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">Penn State</a> found that consuming cinnamon can help reduce the body's negative responses to eating high-fat meals.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266069.php" class="content-link">Read more about cinnamon.</a></p><hr/><h2>Coffee</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Coffee" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-coffee.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-coffee.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-coffee.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-coffee.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-coffee.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-coffee.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270202.php" title="Health benefits and risks of drinking coffee" class="keywords content-link">Coffee</a> is one of the main sources of antioxidants in the U.S. population.</p><p>The potential health benefits of drinking coffee in moderation include: <a href="http://diabetes.diabetesjournals.org/content/60/1/269.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">protecting against type 2 diabetes</a>, <hl-trusted-source source="JAMA" rationale="Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal"><a href="http://jamanetwork.com/journals/jama/fullarticle/192731" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">preventing Parkinson's disease</a></hl-trusted-source>, lowering the <a href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1542356513006095" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">risk of liver cancer</a>, preventing <a href="http://www.gastrojournal.org/article/S0016-5085(13)63555-6/abstract" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">liver disease</a>, and promoting good <a href="http://circheartfailure.ahajournals.org/content/5/4/401.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">heart health</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270202.php" class="content-link">Read more about coffee.</a></p><hr/><h2>Collard greens</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Collard greens" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/collard-greens.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/collard-greens.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/collard-greens.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/collard-greens.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fcollard-greens.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/collard-greens.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Collard greens are part of the cruciferous vegetable family, which also includes kale, broccoli, Brussels sprouts, cabbage, rutabaga, and turnips.</p><p>Collard greens are an extremely rich source of vitamin K and also contain folate, thiamin, niacin, pantothenic acid, choline, phosphorus, and potassium.</p><p>Health benefits of collard greens may include assisting with bone health, reducing cancer risk, helping lower glucose levels in those with diabetes, and improving sleep and mood.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/277957.php" class="content-link">Read more about collard greens.</a></p><hr/><h2>Cranberries</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Cranberries" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-cranberries.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-cranberries.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-cranberries.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-cranberries.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-cranberries.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-cranberries.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Cranberries are a good source of vitamin C, fiber, and vitamin E.</p><p>Studies have found that cranberries can potentially <a href="https://academic.oup.com/nutritionreviews/article-abstract/65/11/490/1907389" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">reduce the risk of cardiovascular disease</a> (CVD), <a href="https://www.mskcc.org/cancer-care/integrative-medicine/herbs/cranberry" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">slow tumor progression</a>, prevent <a href="http://www.nrcresearchpress.com/doi/abs/10.1139/cjm-2012-0744" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">urinary tract infections</a>, and benefit oral health by preventing bacteria from binding to teeth.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/269142.php" class="content-link">Read more about cranberries.</a></p><hr/><h2>Edamame</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Edamame beans and pods." src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/edamame-beans-and-pods.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/edamame-beans-and-pods.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/edamame-beans-and-pods.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/edamame-beans-and-pods.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fedamame-beans-and-pods.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/edamame-beans-and-pods.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/280285.php" title="What are the health benefits of edamame?" class="keywords content-link">Edamame</a> is a young soybean that has been harvested before the beans have had a chance to harden. They can be bought shelled or in the pod, fresh or frozen.</p><p>The potential health benefits of edamame include maintaining a healthy blood pressure, helping with <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/kc/depression-causes-symptoms-treatments-8933" title="What is depression and what can I do about it?" class="keywords content-link">depression</a>, promoting fertility, and decreasing bone loss.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/280285.php" class="content-link">Read more about edamame.</a></p><hr/><h2>Eggplant</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="eggplant" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/eggplant.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/eggplant.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/eggplant.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/eggplant.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Feggplant.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/eggplant.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>The eggplant, also known as aubergine, garden egg, guinea squash, melongene, and brinjal, is usually distinguishable by its signature egg-like shape and vibrant purple color.</p><p>The potential health benefits of eggplant include supporting heart health, maintaining weight and blood cholesterol levels, and anti-cancer effects.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/279359.php" class="content-link">Read more about eggplant.</a></p><hr/><h2>Flaxseed</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Flaxseed" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-flaxseed.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-flaxseed.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-flaxseed.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-flaxseed.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-flaxseed.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-flaxseed.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Flaxseed is not only "an excellent source of two fatty acids that are essential for human health - linoleic acid and alpha-linolenic acid," but also "an excellent source of fiber and a good source of minerals and vitamins," according to the <a href="http://americannutritionassociation.org/newsletter/flaxseed-neglected-food" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">American Nutrition Association</a>.</p><p>The potential health benefits associated with flaxseed include: <a href="http://archive.news.iastate.edu/news/2010/mar/flaxseed" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">lowering cholesterol</a>, protecting <a href="http://cebp.aacrjournals.org/content/cebp/17/12/3577.full.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">against cancer</a>, preventing hot flashes, and improving blood sugar levels.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/263405.php" class="content-link">Read more about flaxseed.</a></p><hr/><h2>Garlic</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Garlic" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-garlic.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-garlic.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-garlic.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-garlic.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-garlic.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-garlic.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Garlic is widely used for several conditions linked to the blood system and heart.</p><p>Studies have found that garlic can potentially be a very <a href="https://academic.oup.com/jac/article/67/8/1915/746474/Antimicrobial-effect-of-diallyl-sulphide-on" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">powerful antibiotic</a>, help protect the heart during cardiac surgery and after a <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/151444.php" title="How to spot and treat a heart attack" class="keywords content-link">heart attack</a>, lower the risk of <a href="http://cancerpreventionresearch.aacrjournals.org/content/canprevres/early/2013/05/08/1940-6207.CAPR-13-0015.full.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">developing lung cancer</a>, and <a href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0955286304000403" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">reduce</a> high cholesterol and blood pressure levels.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/265853.php" class="content-link">Read more about garlic.</a></p><hr/><h2>Ginger</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Ginger" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-ginger.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-ginger.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-ginger.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-ginger.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-ginger.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-ginger.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/265990.php" title="Ginger: Health benefits and dietary tips" class="keywords content-link">Ginger</a> contains a chemical that is used as an ingredient in antacid, laxative, and anti-gas medications.</p><p>Studies have found that ginger can potentially prevent <a href="http://cancerpreventionresearch.aacrjournals.org/content/4/11/1929.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">inflammation of the colon</a>, reduce <a href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1526590009009158" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">exercise-induced muscle pain</a>, help alleviate <a href="https://www.urmc.rochester.edu/news/story/2491/ginger-quells-cancer-patients-nausea-from-chemotherapy.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">nausea caused by chemotherapy</a>, and reduce the severity of <a href="http://www.jpma.org.pk/PdfDownload/3925.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">period pains</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/265990.php" class="content-link">Read more about ginger.</a></p><hr/><h2>Grapes</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Grapes" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-grapes.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-grapes.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-grapes.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-grapes.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-grapes.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-grapes.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>The portability, texture, flavor, and variety of grapes have made them a popular finger food in countries all over the world.</p><p>Studies have associated grapes with the prevention of cancer, heart disease, <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/159283.php" title="What to know about high blood pressure" class="keywords content-link">high blood pressure</a>, and constipation as well as decreasing the risk of obesity and overall mortality.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/271156.php" class="content-link">Read more about grapes.</a></p><hr/><h2>Grapefruit</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="grapefruit" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/grapefruit.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/grapefruit.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/grapefruit.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/grapefruit.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fgrapefruit.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/grapefruit.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Grapefruits are low in calories but full of nutrients. They support clear, healthy skin, help to lower the risk of many diseases and conditions and may even help with weight loss as part of an overall healthy and varied diet.</p><p>The potential health benefits of grapefruit include boosting weight loss, maintaining healthy blood pressure and heart health, and combating free radicals.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/280882.php" class="content-link">Read more about grapefruit.</a></p><hr/><h2>Green Tea</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Green tea" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-green-tea.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-green-tea.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-green-tea.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-green-tea.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-green-tea.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-green-tea.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/269538.php" title="Green tea: Health benefits, side effects, and research" class="keywords content-link">Green tea</a> may well be one of the world's healthiest drinks and contains the highest amount of antioxidants of any tea.</p><p>Studies have found that drinking green tea is associated with a reduced <a href="http://stroke.ahajournals.org/content/early/2013/03/14/STROKEAHA.111.677500.abstract" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">risk of stroke</a>, and may help fight <a href="https://www.cuh.nhs.uk/news/cancer-services/uk-scientists-show-super-foods-proven-beat-prostate-cancer" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">prostate cancer</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/269538.php" class="content-link">Read more about green tea.</a></p><hr/><h2>Honey</h2><span class="css-zya54r"></span><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Honey" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-honey.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-honey.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-honey.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-honey.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-honey.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-honey.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Honey possesses antiseptic and antibacterial properties.</p><p>Studies have found that honey can potentially help prevent <hl-trusted-source source="BMJ" rationale="Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal"><a href="http://www.bmj.com/rapid-response/2011/10/28/oesophagus-heartburn-and-honey" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">GERD</a></hl-trusted-source> (gastroesophageal reflux), shorten the duration of <hl-trusted-source source="BMJ" rationale="Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal"><a href="http://www.bmj.com/content/290/6485/1866.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">bacterial diarrhea</a></hl-trusted-source>, <a href="http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/14651858.CD005083.pub2/full" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">help heal burns</a>, minimize <a href="http://www.karger.com/Article/Abstract/319821" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">seasonal allergies</a>, and <a href="http://www.fasebj.org/content/24/7/2576.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">fight off infections</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/264667.php" class="content-link">Read more about honey.</a></p><hr/><h2>Kale</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Kale" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-kale.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-kale.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-kale.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-kale.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-kale.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-kale.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Kale is a great source of vitamin K, vitamin A, beta-carotene, calcium, and vitamin C.</p><p>The potential health benefits of kale include: reducing the risk of certain cancers, lowering the risk of <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/184130.php" title="What to know about coronary heart disease" class="keywords content-link">coronary artery disease</a>, and lowering levels of bad cholesterol.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270435.php" class="content-link">Read more about kale.</a></p><hr/><h2>Kiwifruit</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Kiwi" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-kiwi.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-kiwi.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-kiwi.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-kiwi.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-kiwi.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-kiwi.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Kiwis are a nutrient dense food, meaning they are high in nutrients and low in calories. The kiwifruit is higher in vitamin C per ounce than most other fruits.</p><p>The potential health benefits of eating kiwis include: maintaining healthy skin tone and texture, reducing blood pressure, and preventing heart disease and <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/7624.php" title="Everything you need to know about stroke" class="keywords content-link">stroke</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/271232.php" class="content-link">Read more about kiwifruit.</a></p><hr/><h2>Mango</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Mango" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mango.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mango.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mango.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mango.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fmango.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mango.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>The <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275921.php" title="Everything you need to know about mangoes" class="keywords content-link">mango</a> is a member of the drupe family, a type of plant food in which an outer fleshy part surrounds a shell (what we sometimes call a pit) with a seed inside. Olives, dates, and coconuts are also types of drupes.</p><p>Many studies have suggested that increasing consumption of plant foods like mangoes decreases the risk of obesity and overall mortality, diabetes, heart disease, and promotes a healthy complexion and hair, increased energy, overall lower weight.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275921.php" class="content-link">Read more about mango.</a></p><hr/><h2>Milk</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Milk" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-milk-glass.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-milk-glass.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-milk-glass.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-milk-glass.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-milk-glass.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-milk-glass.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Dairy products, like milk, are a great dietary source of calcium. Calcium has many functions in the body, but its primary job is the development and maintenance of healthy bones and teeth.</p><p>Calcium is also important for blood-clotting and wound-healing, maintaining normal blood pressure, and muscle contractions, including heartbeat.</p><p>Milk also provides magnesium, phosphorus, vitamin A, riboflavin, vitamins B-6 and B-12.</p><p>The potential health benefits of milk include: maintaining bone, blood pressure, and heart health, and providing an increase in <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/161618.php" title="What are the health benefits of vitamin D?" class="keywords content-link">vitamin D</a>. Deficiency in vitamin D has been associated with depression, chronic <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/248002.php" title="Fatigue: Why am I so tired and what can I do about it?" class="keywords content-link">fatigue</a>, and PMS.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/273451.php" class="content-link">Read more about milk.</a></p><hr/><h2>Milk alternatives</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Coconut milk" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/coconut-milk.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/coconut-milk.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/coconut-milk.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/coconut-milk.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fcoconut-milk.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/coconut-milk.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>There are many reasons you might search for an alternative for dairy, the most common being allergies and <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/180120.php" title="Lactose intolerance: What you need to know" class="keywords content-link">lactose intolerance</a>.</p><p>Some people choose to not consume dairy to follow a vegan diet, which avoids any foods that come from an animal, including milk, cheese, eggs, and honey.</p><p>Others may cut dairy out of their diet to avoid hormones and <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/10278.php" title="What to know about antibiotics" class="keywords content-link">antibiotics</a> in conventional milk, as an <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/107146.php" title="What you need to know about acne" class="keywords content-link">acne</a> treatment, or when following the popular "Paleo" diet.</p><p>Soy isoflavones have been shown to be beneficial in preventing heart disease, and at least 10 milligrams per day can decrease <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/37136.php" title="What to know about breast cancer" class="keywords content-link">breast cancer</a> recurrence by 25 percent. Increased soy consumption may be beneficial for menopausal women.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/273982.php" class="content-link">Read more about alternatives to milk.</a></p><hr/><h2>Mint</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Mint" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mint.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mint.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mint.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mint.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fmint.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mint.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275944.php" title="What are the benefits of mint?" class="keywords content-link">Mint</a>, also known as mentha, is actually a genus of around 15-20 types of plants including peppermint and spearmint. Mint oil is often used in toothpaste, gum, candy, and beauty products while the leaves are used either fresh or dried for teas and food.</p><p>Mint has one of the highest antioxidant capacities of any food. Mint has possible positive effects on allergies, common cold, <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/163484.php" title="What to know about indigestion or dyspepsia" class="keywords content-link">indigestion</a>, <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/37063.php" title="What is irritable bowel syndrome (IBS)?" class="keywords content-link">irritable bowel syndrome</a> (IBS), and skin.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275944.php" class="content-link">Read more about mint.</a></p><hr/><h2>Mushrooms</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Mushrooms" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mushrooms.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mushrooms.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mushrooms.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mushrooms.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fmushrooms.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mushrooms.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Mushrooms, though classified as vegetables in the food world, are not technically plants. They belong to the fungi kingdom and provide several important nutrients.</p><p>The potential health benefits of mushrooms include helping to inhibit the growth of cancer cells, regulating blood pressure, and improving immune responses to infection.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/278858.php" class="content-link">Read more about mushrooms.</a></p><hr/><h2>Oats</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Oats" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oats.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oats.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oats.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oats.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-oats.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oats.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Oats contain high levels of a type of fiber known as beta-glucan. Beta-glucan is known to help lower levels of bad cholesterol.</p><p>The potential health benefits of oats include: reducing the risk of coronary artery disease, lowering the risk of <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/155598.php" title="Colorectal cancer: What you need to know" class="keywords content-link">colorectal cancer</a>, and lowering blood pressure.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270680.php" class="content-link">Read more about oats.</a></p><hr/><h2>Oily fish</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Mackerel fishes" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-mackerel-fish.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-mackerel-fish.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-mackerel-fish.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-mackerel-fish.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-mackerel-fish.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-mackerel-fish.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Oily fish, such as salmon or mackerel, is an excellent source of <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/40253.php" title="Can fish oils and omega-3 oils benefit our health?" class="keywords content-link">omega-3</a> oils and lean protein.</p><p>Potential health benefits of eating oily fish include: <a href="http://ajpregu.physiology.org/content/304/7/R523.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">preventing cardiovascular disease</a>, <a href="http://ard.bmj.com/content/73/11/1949.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">reducing the risk of rheumatoid arthritis</a>, boosting infant sensory, cognitive, and <a href="http://ajcn.nutrition.org/content/93/5/1025.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">motor development</a>, <hl-trusted-source source="PloS One" rationale="Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal"><a href="http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0046832" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">improving memory</a></hl-trusted-source>, <a href="http://iovs.arvojournals.org/article.aspx?articleid=2188773" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">protecting vision</a>, and preventing <a href="https://academic.oup.com/carcin/article-abstract/34/12/2716/2464040" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">oral and skin cancers</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/9978.php" class="content-link">Read more about oily fish.</a></p><hr/><h2>Olive oil</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="olive-oil" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-olive-oil.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-olive-oil.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-olive-oil.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-olive-oil.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-olive-oil.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-olive-oil.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>People who regularly consume olive oil are at a lower risk of developing cardiovascular diseases, including <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/150109.php" title="Everything you need to know about hypertension" class="keywords content-link">hypertension</a> (high blood pressure), stroke, and <a href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1043661807000333" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">hyperlipidemia</a> (high blood cholesterol and triglyceride levels).</p><p>In addition, olive oil intake may help treat inflammation, endothelial dysfunction (problems with the inner linings of blood vessels), thrombosis and <a href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1043661807000333" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">carbohydrate metabolism</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266258.php" class="content-link">Read more about olive oil.</a></p><hr/><h2>Onions</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Onions" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/onions.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/onions.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/onions.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/onions.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fonions.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/onions.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/276714.php" title="Health benefits and risks of onions" class="keywords content-link">Onions</a> can vary in size, shape, color, and flavor. The most common types are red, yellow, and white onion.</p><p>Flavors can vary from sweet and juicy with a mild flavor to sharp, spicy, and pungent, often depending on the season in which they are grown and consumed. An estimated 105 billion pounds of onions are harvested each year worldwide.</p><p>The possible health benefits of consuming onions include lowering the risk of several types of cancer, improving mood, and maintaining the health of skin and hair</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/276714.php" class="content-link">Read more about onions.</a></p><hr/><h2>Oranges</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="orange" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oranges.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oranges.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oranges.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oranges.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-oranges.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oranges.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>An orange has over 170 different phytochemicals and more than 60 flavonoids, many of which have been shown to have anti-inflammatory properties and strong antioxidant effects.</p><p>Oranges also contain thiamin, riboflavin, niacin, vitamin B-6, folate, pantothenic acid, phosphorus, magnesium, manganese, selenium, and copper. Because of their high vitamin C content (over twice the daily need), oranges are associated with boosting the immune system.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/272782.php" class="content-link">Read more about oranges.</a></p><hr/><h2>Oregano</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="oregano" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oregano.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oregano.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oregano.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oregano.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-oregano.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oregano.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Oregano is a rich source of vitamin K and dietary antioxidants.</p><p>Studies have found that oregano has <a href="http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/jf0510079" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">antimicrobial activity</a>, <a href="http://www.pnas.org/content/105/26/9099.short" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">anti-inflammatory properties</a>, and components in oregano may help slow down or prevent the progression of disease in patients with <hl-trusted-source source="PloS One" rationale="Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal"><a href="http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0068808" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">breast cancer</a></hl-trusted-source>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266259.php" class="content-link">Read more about oregano.</a></p><hr/><p><strong></strong></p><h2>Papaya</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Papaya fruit cut in half with seeds showing." src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/papaya-fruit-cut-in-half-with-seeds-showing.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/papaya-fruit-cut-in-half-with-seeds-showing.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/papaya-fruit-cut-in-half-with-seeds-showing.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/papaya-fruit-cut-in-half-with-seeds-showing.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fpapaya-fruit-cut-in-half-with-seeds-showing.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/papaya-fruit-cut-in-half-with-seeds-showing.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275517.php" title="What are the health benefits of papaya?" class="keywords content-link">Papayas</a> grow in tropical climates and are also known as papaws or pawpaws.</p><p>The possible health benefits of consuming papaya include a reduced risk of heart disease, diabetes, cancer, aiding in digestion, improving blood glucose control in people with diabetes, lowering blood pressure, and improving wound healing.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275517.php" class="content-link">Read more about papaya.</a></p><hr/><span class="css-zya54r"></span><h2>Peaches</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Two peaches" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/two-peaches.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/two-peaches.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/two-peaches.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/two-peaches.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Ftwo-peaches.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/two-peaches.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Peaches are a characteristically fuzzy fruit native to northwest China. They are a member of the stone fruit family, meaning that they have one large middle seed, along with cherries, apricots, plums, and nectarines.</p><p>One medium peach contains 2 percent or more daily value of vitamins E and K, niacin, folate, iron, choline, potassium, magnesium, phosphorus, manganese, zinc, and copper. They have been shown to ward off obesity-related diseases, such as diabetes, metabolic syndrome, and cardiovascular disease.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/274620.php" class="content-link">Read more about peaches.</a></p><hr/><h2>Peppermint</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="peppermint" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-peppermint.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-peppermint.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-peppermint.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-peppermint.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-peppermint.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-peppermint.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Peppermint is used as a traditional or folk remedy for several conditions and illnesses because of its calming effects.</p><p>The potential health benefits of peppermint include: treating the symptoms of <a href="http://europepmc.org/abstract/med/23416804" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">irritable bowel syndrome</a> (IBS), calming skin irritation and itchiness, and preventing the onset of <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/73936.php" title="What is causing this headache?" class="keywords content-link">headaches</a> and <a href="http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/head.12091/full" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">associated symptoms</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/265214.php" class="content-link">Read more about peppermint.</a></p><hr/><h2>Pineapple</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Pineapple" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/pineapple.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/pineapple.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/pineapple.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/pineapple.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fpineapple.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/pineapple.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Pineapple is a source of important vitamins and minerals such as thiamin, riboflavin, vitamin B-6, folate, pantothenic acid, magnesium, manganese, and potassium. It also contains antioxidants and polyphenols, such as beta-carotene.</p><p>Fresh pineapple is the only known source of an enzyme called bromelain, which may help reduce joint pain and the symptoms of arthritis, reduce inflammation, inhibit <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/249141.php" title="What are the different types of tumor?" class="keywords content-link">tumor</a> growth, and shorten recovery time following plastic surgery.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/276903.php" class="content-link">Read more about pineapple.</a></p><hr/><h2>Potatoes</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Potatoes" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/potatoes.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/potatoes.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/potatoes.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/potatoes.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fpotatoes.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/potatoes.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Along with the tomato and eggplant, the potato plant belongs to the nightshade family, of which some species are truly poisonous. Today, potatoes are one of the cheapest universal crops to produce and are available year-round.</p><p>The health benefits of consuming potatoes include maintaining bone structure, supporting heart health, reducing chronic inflammation, and preventing constipation.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/280579.php" class="content-link">Read more about potatoes.</a></p><hr/><h2>Pumpkin</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Pumpkins" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/pumpkins.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/pumpkins.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/pumpkins.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/pumpkins.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fpumpkins.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/pumpkins.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/279610.php" title="What are the health benefits of pumpkins?" class="keywords content-link">Pumpkin</a> is an extremely nutrient dense food, meaning it is chock-full of vitamins and minerals but low in calories. There are many creative ways pumpkin can be incorporated into your diet, including desserts, soups, salads, preserves, and even as a substitute for butter.</p><p>The potential health benefits of pumpkin including supporting heart health, eye health, promoting fertility, and giving immunity a boost.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/279610.php" class="content-link">Read more about pumpkin.</a></p><hr/><h2>Quinoa</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="White and red quinoa" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/white-and-red-quinoa.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/white-and-red-quinoa.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/white-and-red-quinoa.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/white-and-red-quinoa.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fwhite-and-red-quinoa.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/white-and-red-quinoa.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Nutritionally, <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/274745.php" title="Health benefits of quinoa" class="keywords content-link">quinoa</a> is considered a whole grain. Whole grains include the entire intact grain seed without removing any of its parts.</p><p>In contrast, when grains are milled or refined like white breads, white rice, and white pasta, they have been processed to create a finer, lighter texture, and are not as nutrient dense. Quinoa is also a great source of protein.</p><p>Consuming 2-3 servings of whole grain foods per day can reduce the risk of cardiovascular disease, <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/info/diabetes/type2diabetes.php" title="What is type 2 diabetes?" class="keywords content-link">type 2 diabetes</a>, high blood pressure, <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/150496.php" title="Everything you need to know about colon cancer" class="keywords content-link">colon cancer</a>, and obesity.  Many studies have shown that as whole grain intake increases, the risk for all five of these lifestyle-related conditions decreases. </p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/274745" class="content-link">Read more about quinoa.</a></p><hr/><h2>Rosemary</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="rosemary" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-rosemary.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-rosemary.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-rosemary.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-rosemary.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-rosemary.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-rosemary.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Rosemary is a rich source of antioxidants and anti-inflammatory compounds.</p><p>Studies have found that rosemary may potentially help <a href="http://umm.edu/health/medical/altmed/herb/rosemary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">treat indigestion</a>, enhance <a href="http://journals.sagepub.com/doi/abs/10.1177/2045125312436573" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">memory and concentration</a>, provide <hl-trusted-source source="PubMed Central" rationale="Highly respected database from the National Institutes of Health"><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3652539/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">neurological protection</a></hl-trusted-source>, and provide protection against <a href="http://iovs.arvojournals.org/article.aspx?articleid=2127627" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">macular degeneration</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266370.php" class="content-link">Read more about rosemary.</a></p><hr/><h2>Sage</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="sage" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-sage.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-sage.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-sage.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-sage.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-sage.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-sage.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Sage is rich in antioxidants (apigenin, diosmetin, and luteolin) and important nutrients, such as vitamin K.</p><p>Studies have found that sage may potentially improve memory and information processing among people who have mild <a href="http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1046/j.1365-2710.2003.00463.x/full" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">Alzheimer's disease</a> and help lower cholesterol and triglyceride levels in patients with <a href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0965229913001180" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">type 2 diabetes</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266480.php" class="content-link">Read more about sage.</a></p><hr/><h2>Spearmint</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="spearmint" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-spearmint.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-spearmint.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-spearmint.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-spearmint.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-spearmint.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-spearmint.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Spearmint contains high amounts of vitamins, antioxidants, and other vital nutrients.</p><p>Studies have found that spearmint may potentially have <a href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S030881460500885X" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">antioxidant and antifungal</a> properties, reduce symptoms of nausea and other <a href="http://www.ipcbee.com/vol15/10-U00041.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">digestive problems</a>, and treat <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/6376599.stm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">hirsutism</a> (abnormal hair growth).</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266128.php" class="content-link">Read more about spearmint.</a></p><hr/><h2>Spinach</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Spinach" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-spinach.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-spinach.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-spinach.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-spinach.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-spinach.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-spinach.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Spinach is one of the best sources of dietary magnesium and calcium.</p><p>The potential health benefits of spinach include: helping manage diabetes, helping preventing cancer, reducing the risk of asthma, lowering the risk of blood pressure, and improving bone health.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270609.php" class="content-link">Read more about spinach.</a></p><hr/><h2>Strawberries</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Strawberries" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-strawberries.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-strawberries.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-strawberries.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-strawberries.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-strawberries.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-strawberries.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Strawberries are one of the most popular, refreshing, and healthy treats on the planet; they contain many vitamins and antioxidants that can be beneficial for your health.</p><p>The potential health benefits of strawberries include: reducing the risk of heart disease, stroke, cancer, blood pressure, constipation, allergies, diabetes, and depression.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/271285.php" class="content-link">Read more about strawberries.</a></p><hr/><h2>Sweet potatoes</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="sweet potatoes" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/sweet-potatoes.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/sweet-potatoes.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/sweet-potatoes.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/sweet-potatoes.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Fsweet-potatoes.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/sweet-potatoes.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Sweet potatoes pack a powerful nutritional punch. They have over 400 percent of your daily needs for vitamin A in one medium potato, plus high levels of fiber and potassium.</p><p>The potential health benefits of sweet potatoes include a protective role against prostate cancer, promoting fertility, boosting immunity, and supporting vision.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/281438.php" class="content-link">Read more about sweet potatoes.</a></p><hr/><h2>Thyme</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="sprigs of thyme" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-thyme.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-thyme.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-thyme.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-thyme.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-thyme.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-thyme.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Thyme preparations may be more effective than acne prescription creams, <a href="http://www.leedsbeckett.ac.uk/news/thyme-for-a-more-natural-cure-to-acne/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">according to scientists</a> at Leeds Metropolitan University in England.</p><p>Studies have found that thyme may potentially protect against <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11130-013-0368-7" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">hypertension</a>, help fight off <a href="http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/ben/mc/2011/00000007/00000006/art00017" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">foodborne bacterial infections</a>, and induce cell death in <a href="http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/01635581.2012.719658" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="content-link">breast cancer cells</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266016.php" class="content-link">Read more about thyme.</a></p><hr/><h2>Tofu</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="Tofu" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/tofu.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/tofu.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/tofu.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/tofu.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269%2F269143%2Ftofu.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/tofu.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Tofu, made from soybean curds, is naturally gluten-free and low calorie, contains no cholesterol, and is an excellent source of protein, iron, and calcium.</p><p>The isoflavones (a type of compound called phytoestrogens) in soy foods have been linked to a decreased risk for osteoporosis, while the calcium and magnesium in soy may help to lessen PMS symptoms, regulate blood sugar, and prevent <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/148373.php" title="Everything you need to know about migraines" class="keywords content-link">migraine</a> headaches.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/278340.php" class="content-link">Read more about tofu.</a></p><hr/><h2>Tomatoes</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="tomatoes" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/273031-tomatoes.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/273031-tomatoes.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/273031-tomatoes.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/273031-tomatoes.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F273031-tomatoes.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/273031-tomatoes.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>The tomato has been referred to as a "functional food," a food that goes beyond providing just basic nutrition, additionally preventing chronic disease and delivering other health benefits, due to beneficial phytochemicals such as lycopene.</p><p>Tomatoes are a rich source of vitamins A and C and <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/219853.php" title="What to know about folic acid" class="keywords content-link">folic acid</a>. Tomatoes contain a wide array of beneficial nutrients and antioxidants, including alpha-lipoic acid, lycopene, choline, folic acid, beta-carotene, and lutein.</p><p>The benefits of consuming fruits and vegetables of all kinds, including tomatoes, are infinite. As plant food consumption goes up, the risk of heart disease, diabetes, and cancer goes down.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/273031.php" class="content-link">Read more about tomatoes.</a></p><hr/><h2>Watermelon</h2><figure class="css-oei5ji"><span class="css-rwmw5v"><span class="css-17kbi8i"><lazy-image alt="slices of watermelon" src="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-watermelon.jpg?w=1155" srcSet="//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-watermelon.jpg?w=1845 879w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-watermelon.jpg?w=1575 750w,//i0.wp.com/cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-watermelon.jpg?w=1575 750w" className="css-iq3uei"></lazy-image></span><span class="css-18moxll"><a class="icon-hl-pinterest css-1fquaub" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2F269143.php&amp;media=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com%2Fcontent%2Fimages%2Farticles%2F269143-watermelon.jpg&amp;description=The%20health%20benefits%20of%20popular%20foods" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" title="Share on Pinterest" data-pin-custom="true" data-share-url="https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-watermelon.jpg"><span class="css-8yl26h">Share on Pinterest</span></a></span></span></figure><p>Watermelon contains thiamin, riboflavin, niacin, vitamin B-6, folate, pantothenic acid, magnesium, phosphorus, potassium, zinc, copper, manganese, selenium, choline, lycopene, and betaine. Watermelon is a good source of lycopene.</p><p>The possible health benefits of watermelon include asthma prevention, reduction of high blood pressure, regulation of digestion, inflammation reduction, and promotes healthy hair and skin. Watermelon is also one of the best sources lycopene.</p><p><a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266886.php" class="content-link">Read more about watermelon.</a></p><span class="css-zya54r"></span></article></div></div><section class="css-11iztoc"><div class="css-1w9mrx"><section class="css-1m6cg88"><div class="css-4nmqvw"><div class="css-12r7hj0">Medically reviewed by <a class="css-0 css-1g08k51" href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/reviewers">Nata