</script><script async="" src="//c.amazon-adsystem.com/aax2/apstag.js"></script><script>module={};__NEXT_DATA__={"buildId":"cec05609-81cd-45a7-b923-681498e2593b","props":{"adTargeting":{"title":"The health benefits of popular foods","canonical":"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/269143.php","pageTemplate":"Standard Article","logMoreMetrics":true,"isCPUV":false,"newsletterMeta":{"source":"article_modal_newsletter_btn","lists":["_MNT Master List (All data)","MNT Daily News","MNT Weekly News"],"title":"MNT"},"newsletter":{"tags":"","categories":""},"targeting":{"k1":"diettypes","k2":"weightmanagement","msiteactive":"false"},"categories":[{"name":"Nutrition / Diet","link":"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/categories/nutrition-diet","parent":0}]},"ga":{"k1":"diettypes","k2":"weightmanagement","contentType":"Standard Article","author":"Joseph Nordqvist","sponsoredProgramId":"","articleId":269143,"mainContentCategoryTags":"nutrition-diet","publishedDate":"2017-09-01","updatedDate":"2017-09-01","medReviewer":"Natalie Olsen, RD, LD, ACSM EP-C","category":"Nutrition / Diet"},"lang":"en","data":{"title":["How can these popular foods benefit our health?"],"pinterestImage":"https://assets.healthline.com/content/hl_sharing_v2.jpg","hideFeedback":true,"body":[{"type":"tag","tagName":"deck","widget":{"content":["Though the field of medicine continues to advance and branch out in many ways, nutritionists and health experts continue to praise the benefits of certain foods. In fact, eating healthfully has been shown to reduce the risk of obesity, cardiovascular illnesses, and even certain types of cancer."],"widgetFormat":"deck"}},{"tagName":"p","source":" However, understanding which foods to eat for specific benefits can sometimes be difficult, which is why \u003cem\u003eMedical News Today\u003c/em\u003e previously supplied a list of the \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/245259.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003etop 10 healthy foods\u003c/a\u003e. "},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/popular-healthy-foods-laid-out-on-white-background.jpg","alt":"popular healthy foods laid out on white background"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":" Now, \u003cem\u003eMNT\u003c/em\u003e specifies the health benefits of a much wider range of foods."},{"tagName":"p","source":"We provide a cornucopia of delicious and nutritious options for individuals who wish to boost their health by eating healthfully. "},{"tagName":"p","source":"Below is a list of foods along with information regarding their potential health benefits. "},{"tagName":"p","source":" Note that this article contains summaries and you should click through to read individual articles containing the full list of possible health benefits."},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Almonds"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-almonds.jpg","alt":"Almonds"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Almonds are a rich source of \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/195878.php\" title=\"Vitamins: What are they and what do they do?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003evitamin\u003c/a\u003e E, \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/288165.php\" title=\"Health benefits and risks of copper\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ecopper\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/286839.php\" title=\"Why do we need magnesium?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003emagnesium\u003c/a\u003e, good quality protein, and healthy unsaturated fatty acids."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have revealed that almonds can potentially help \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"PubMed Central\" rationale=\"Highly respected database from the National Institutes of Health\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12221048\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eprevent cardiovascular diseases\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e, cut the risk of \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/info/cancer-oncology/\" title=\"What is Cancer?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ecancer\u003c/a\u003e, and help \u003ca href=\"http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMoa1307352\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eprolong life\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/269468.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about almonds.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Apples"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-apples.jpg","alt":"Apple and apple slices"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Apples are sometimes called \"nutritional powerhouses\" because of their impressive nutritional profile."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Apples contain about 14 percent of our daily needs of Vitamin C (a powerful natural \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/301506.php\" title=\"How can antioxidants benefit our health?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eantioxidant\u003c/a\u003e), B-complex vitamins, dietary fiber, phytonutrients (which help protect the body from the detrimental effects of free radicals), and minerals such as \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/248958.php\" title=\"Calcium: Health benefits, foods, and deficiency\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ecalcium\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/287212.php\" title=\"Everything you need to know about potassium\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003epotassium\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have revealed that eating apples can potentially help \u003ca href=\"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1750-3841.2007.00632.x/full\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eprevent dementia\u003c/a\u003e and reduce the \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"PubMed Central\" rationale=\"Highly respected database from the National Institutes of Health\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10822289\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003erisk of stroke\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/info/diabetes/\" title=\"What is Diabetes?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ediabetes\u003c/a\u003e\u003cb\u003e.\u003c/b\u003e"},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/267290.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about apples.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Arugula"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/arugula.jpg","alt":"arugula"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Along with other leafy greens, arugula contains very high nitrate levels (more than 250 milligrams per 100 grams). High intakes of dietary nitrate have been shown to lower \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270644.php\" title=\"What is a normal blood pressure?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eblood pressure\u003c/a\u003e, reduce the amount of oxygen needed during exercise, and enhance athletic performance."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of arugula include lowering the risk of cancer, preventing \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/155646.php\" title=\"What to know about osteoporosis\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eosteoporosis\u003c/a\u003e, and improving muscle oxygenation during exercise."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/282769.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about arugula.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Asparagus"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-asparagus.jpg","alt":"Asparagus"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Asparagus is very rich in dietary fiber and contains high levels of vitamin B6, calcium, zinc, and magnesium."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of asparagus include: reducing the risk of diabetes, preventing \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/154193.php\" title=\"How do you get kidney stones?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ekidney stones\u003c/a\u003e, and lowering the risk of neural tube defects in babies."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Asparagus is also a natural diuretic, which can help with fluid balance in the body and influence blood pressure and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/159111.php\" title=\"Everything you need to know about edema\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eedema\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270805.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about asparagus.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Bananas"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-bananas.jpg","alt":"Bananas"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/271157.php\" title=\"Benefits and health risks of bananas\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eBananas\u003c/a\u003e are naturally free of fat, \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/9152.php\" title=\"What causes high cholesterol?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003echolesterol\u003c/a\u003e, and sodium, and very rich in potassium."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of bananas include: lowering blood pressure, reducing the risk of developing \u003ca href=\"http://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/142595.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"content-link\"\u003echildhood leukemia\u003c/a\u003e, and supporting heart health."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/271157.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about bananas.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Basil"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-basil.jpg","alt":"Basil leaves"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Basil is rich in vitamin A, vitamin K, vitamin C, magnesium, iron, potassium, and calcium."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have revealed that basil can potentially \u003ca href=\"http://ijpp.com/IJPP archives/2005_49_2/125-131.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ereduce inflammation and swelling\u003c/a\u003e, prevent the harmful \u003ca href=\"http://www.phytojournal.com/archives/?year=2013\u0026vol=2\u0026issue=2\u0026part=B\u0026ArticleId=152\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eeffects of aging\u003c/a\u003e, and may be useful in treating \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/7621.php\" title=\"What are the causes and types of arthritis?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003earthritis\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"http://www.pnas.org/content/105/26/9099.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003einflammatory bowel diseases\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266425.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about basil.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Beetroot"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/beetroot.jpg","alt":"Beetroot"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Beetroot, also known simply as the beet, has been gaining in popularity as a new super food due to recent studies claiming that beets and beetroot juice can improve athletic performance, lower blood pressure and increase blood flow."},{"tagName":"p","source":"This is partly due to its high content of nitrates, which \u003ca href=\"http://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2125.2012.04420.x\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eincrease nitric oxide\u003c/a\u003e in the body and play a substantial role in heart and vascular health."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Beetroot is a rich source of \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/287677.php\" title=\"Why is folate good for you?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003efolate\u003c/a\u003e and manganese, and also contains thiamine, riboflavin, vitamin B-6, pantothenic acid, choline, betaine, magnesium, phosphorus, potassium, zinc, copper, and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/287842.php\" title=\"Selenium: What it does and how much you need\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eselenium\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/277432.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about beetroot.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Bok choy"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/bok-choy.jpg","alt":"bok choy"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Bok choy belongs to the cruciferous vegetable family, which also includes \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270435.php\" title=\"What are the health benefits of kale?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ekale\u003c/a\u003e, broccoli, cauliflower, Brussels sprouts, cabbage, collard greens, rutabaga, and turnips."},{"tagName":"p","source":"These \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/160774.php\" title=\"Nutrition: What is it and why is it important?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003enutrition\u003c/a\u003e powerhouses supply loads of nutrients for little \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/245588.php\" title=\"How many calories should I eat a day?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ecalories\u003c/a\u003e. If you are trying to eat healthier, cruciferous vegetables like bok choy should be at the very top of your grocery list."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/280948.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about bok choy.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Broccoli"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-broccoli.jpg","alt":"Ripe broccoli"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Broccoli contains high levels of fiber (both soluble and insoluble) and is a rich source of vitamin C."},{"tagName":"p","source":"In addition, broccoli is rich in vitamin A, iron, vitamin K, B-complex vitamins, zinc, phosphorus, and phytonutrients."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have found that broccoli can potentially help \u003ca href=\"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/art.38133/full\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eprevent osteoarthritis\u003c/a\u003e, protect skin against the \u003ca href=\"http://www.hopkinsmedicine.org/news/media/releases/Broccoli_SproutDerived_Extract_Protects_Against_Ultraviolet_Radiation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eeffects of UV light\u003c/a\u003e, reverse \u003ca href=\"http://diabetes.diabetesjournals.org/content/57/10/2809.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ediabetes heart damage\u003c/a\u003e, and reduce \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"Journal of Nutrition\" rationale=\"Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://academic.oup.com/jnci/article/91/7/605/2543972/Fruit-and-Vegetable-Intake-and-Incidence-of\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ebladder cancer risk\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266765.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about broccoli.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Cantaloupe"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cantaloupe.jpg","alt":"Cantaloupe"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Cantaloupes are also commonly known as muskmelons, mush melons, rock melons, and Persian melons. They are a member of the botanical family Cucurbitaceae, along with honeydew and watermelons."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Cantaloupe contains an abundance of antioxidants, including choline, zeaxanthin, and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/252758.php\" title=\"All you need to know about beta carotene\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ebeta-carotene\u003c/a\u003e, all of which protect against a range of diseases and conditions from the common cold to cancer."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Potential health benefits of cantaloupe include lowering risk of developing \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/info/asthma/\" title=\"What is Asthma?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003easthma\u003c/a\u003e, managing blood pressure, aiding digestion, keeping hydrated, and reducing \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/248423.php\" title=\"Everything you need to know about inflammation\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003einflammation\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/279176.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about cantaloupe.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Carrots"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-carrots.jpg","alt":"Carrots"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Carrots are a great source of vitamin A. They provide 210 percent of an average adult's needs for the day."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of carrots include: \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"PubMed Central\" rationale=\"Highly respected database from the National Institutes of Health\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/3818153\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003epreventing lung cancer\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e, destroying \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/142595.php\" title=\"What to know about leukemia\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eleukemia\u003c/a\u003e cells and \u003ca href=\"http://online.liebertpub.com/doi/abs/10.1089/jmf.2010.0284\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003einhibiting their progression\u003c/a\u003e, and helping to restore vision."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270191.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about carrots.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Cauliflower"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cauliflower.jpg","alt":"cauliflower"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Cauliflowers are a member of the brassica family, more commonly known as cruciferous vegetables."},{"tagName":"p","source":"They contain antioxidants and phytonutrients that can protect against cancer."},{"tagName":"p","source":"They also contain fiber that helps with satiety, weight loss, and a healthy digestive tract, choline that is essential for learning and memory, as well as many other important nutrients."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of cauliflower include preventing mutations and reducing \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/145855.php\" title=\"Why stress happens and how to manage it\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003estress\u003c/a\u003e from free radicals, preventing \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/150322.php\" title=\"What to know about constipation\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003econstipation\u003c/a\u003e, and helping memory."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/282844.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about cauliflower.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Celery"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-celery.jpg","alt":"Celery"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Celery is a very rich source of antioxidants, electrolytes, and vitamin K. Also, thanks to its high water content, it can help rehydrate."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of celery include: lowering blood pressure, preventing cancer, and soothing joint pain."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270678.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about celery.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Chickpeas"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/chickpeas.jpg","alt":"chickpeas"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Originally cultivated in the Mediterranean and the Middle East, chickpeas, also known as garbanzo beans, have spread their culinary influence throughout the world."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of chickpeas include improved glucose levels, lipids, and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/info/diabetes/whatisinsulin.php\" title=\"What is insulin?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003einsulin\u003c/a\u003e levels for diabetes, maintaining bone strength and heart health."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/280244.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about chickpeas.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Chives"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/bunch-of-chives.jpg","alt":"Bunch of chives"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275009.php\" title=\"Health benefits of chives\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eChives\u003c/a\u003e are a nutrient-dense food, meaning that while they are low in calories, they are high in beneficial nutrients like vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of chives include potential beneficial and preventative effects against cancer, \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/150086.php\" title=\"What's to know about prostate cancer?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eprostate cancer\u003c/a\u003e, esophageal and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/257341.php\" title=\"What to know about stomach cancer\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003estomach cancer\u003c/a\u003e, and positive effects on sleep and mood."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275009.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about chives.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Chocolate"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-chocolate.jpg","alt":"Chocolate"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Chocolate is rich in antioxidants. Despite its bad reputation for causing weight gain, there are a number of health benefits associated with its consumption (particularly dark chocolate)."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential benefits of eating chocolate include: lowering cholesterol levels, preventing cognitive decline, and reducing the risk of cardiovascular problems."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270272.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about chocolate.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Cilantro"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/cilantro.jpg","alt":"Cilantro"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Known as coriander in the United Kingdom, cilantro comes from the plant \u003cem\u003eCoriandrum sativum\u003c/em\u003e. In the United States, the leaves of the plant are referred to as cilantro (the Spanish translation), and the seeds are referred to as coriander."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Many studies have suggested that increasing consumption of plant foods like cilantro decreases the risk of \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/info/obesity/how-much-should-i-weigh.php\" title=\"How Much Should I Weigh?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eobesity\u003c/a\u003e, overall mortality, diabetes, and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/237191.php\" title=\"Everything you need to know about heart disease\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eheart disease\u003c/a\u003e while promoting a healthy skin and hair, increased energy, and overall lower weight."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/277627.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about cilantro.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Cinnamon"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-cinnamon.jpg","alt":"Cinnamon sticks"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have found that \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266069.php\" title=\"What are the health benefits of cinnamon?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ecinnamon\u003c/a\u003e can potentially be effective \u003ca href=\"https://search.proquest.com/openview/4ccae43b4086ca488297d37a9e622c3a/1?pq-origsite=gscholar\u0026cbl=37533\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eagainst HIV\u003c/a\u003e, improve glucose and lipid levels in patients \u003ca href=\"http://care.diabetesjournals.org/content/26/12/3215.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ewith type 2 diabetes\u003c/a\u003e, help \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"PloS One\" rationale=\"Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0016564\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eprevent Alzheimer's disease\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e, and stop the destructive \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"PubMed Central\" rationale=\"Highly respected database from the National Institutes of Health\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4568834/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eprocess of multiple sclerosis\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e (MS)."},{"tagName":"p","source":"In addition, researchers at \u003ca href=\"http://jn.nutrition.org/content/141/8/1451.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ePenn State\u003c/a\u003e found that consuming cinnamon can help reduce the body's negative responses to eating high-fat meals."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266069.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about cinnamon.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Coffee"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-coffee.jpg","alt":"Coffee"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270202.php\" title=\"Health benefits and risks of drinking coffee\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eCoffee\u003c/a\u003e is one of the main sources of antioxidants in the U.S. population."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of drinking coffee in moderation include: \u003ca href=\"http://diabetes.diabetesjournals.org/content/60/1/269.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eprotecting against type 2 diabetes\u003c/a\u003e, \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"JAMA\" rationale=\"Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://jamanetwork.com/journals/jama/fullarticle/192731\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003epreventing Parkinson's disease\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e, lowering the \u003ca href=\"http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1542356513006095\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003erisk of liver cancer\u003c/a\u003e, preventing \u003ca href=\"http://www.gastrojournal.org/article/S0016-5085(13)63555-6/abstract\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eliver disease\u003c/a\u003e, and promoting good \u003ca href=\"http://circheartfailure.ahajournals.org/content/5/4/401.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eheart health\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270202.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about coffee.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Collard greens"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/collard-greens.jpg","alt":"Collard greens"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Collard greens are part of the cruciferous vegetable family, which also includes kale, broccoli, Brussels sprouts, cabbage, rutabaga, and turnips."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Collard greens are an extremely rich source of vitamin K and also contain folate, thiamin, niacin, pantothenic acid, choline, phosphorus, and potassium."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Health benefits of collard greens may include assisting with bone health, reducing cancer risk, helping lower glucose levels in those with diabetes, and improving sleep and mood."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/277957.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about collard greens.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Cranberries"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-cranberries.jpg","alt":"Cranberries"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Cranberries are a good source of vitamin C, fiber, and vitamin E."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have found that cranberries can potentially \u003ca href=\"https://academic.oup.com/nutritionreviews/article-abstract/65/11/490/1907389\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ereduce the risk of cardiovascular disease\u003c/a\u003e (CVD), \u003ca href=\"https://www.mskcc.org/cancer-care/integrative-medicine/herbs/cranberry\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eslow tumor progression\u003c/a\u003e, prevent \u003ca href=\"http://www.nrcresearchpress.com/doi/abs/10.1139/cjm-2012-0744\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eurinary tract infections\u003c/a\u003e, and benefit oral health by preventing bacteria from binding to teeth."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/269142.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about cranberries.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Edamame"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/edamame-beans-and-pods.jpg","alt":"Edamame beans and pods."},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/280285.php\" title=\"What are the health benefits of edamame?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eEdamame\u003c/a\u003e is a young soybean that has been harvested before the beans have had a chance to harden. They can be bought shelled or in the pod, fresh or frozen."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of edamame include maintaining a healthy blood pressure, helping with \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/kc/depression-causes-symptoms-treatments-8933\" title=\"What is depression and what can I do about it?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003edepression\u003c/a\u003e, promoting fertility, and decreasing bone loss."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/280285.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about edamame.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Eggplant"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/eggplant.jpg","alt":"eggplant"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"The eggplant, also known as aubergine, garden egg, guinea squash, melongene, and brinjal, is usually distinguishable by its signature egg-like shape and vibrant purple color."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of eggplant include supporting heart health, maintaining weight and blood cholesterol levels, and anti-cancer effects."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/279359.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about eggplant.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Flaxseed"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-flaxseed.jpg","alt":"Flaxseed"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Flaxseed is not only \"an excellent source of two fatty acids that are essential for human health - linoleic acid and alpha-linolenic acid,\" but also \"an excellent source of fiber and a good source of minerals and vitamins,\" according to the \u003ca href=\"http://americannutritionassociation.org/newsletter/flaxseed-neglected-food\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eAmerican Nutrition Association\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits associated with flaxseed include: \u003ca href=\"http://archive.news.iastate.edu/news/2010/mar/flaxseed\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003elowering cholesterol\u003c/a\u003e, protecting \u003ca href=\"http://cebp.aacrjournals.org/content/cebp/17/12/3577.full.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eagainst cancer\u003c/a\u003e, preventing hot flashes, and improving blood sugar levels."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/263405.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about flaxseed.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Garlic"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-garlic.jpg","alt":"Garlic"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Garlic is widely used for several conditions linked to the blood system and heart."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have found that garlic can potentially be a very \u003ca href=\"https://academic.oup.com/jac/article/67/8/1915/746474/Antimicrobial-effect-of-diallyl-sulphide-on\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003epowerful antibiotic\u003c/a\u003e, help protect the heart during cardiac surgery and after a \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/151444.php\" title=\"How to spot and treat a heart attack\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eheart attack\u003c/a\u003e, lower the risk of \u003ca href=\"http://cancerpreventionresearch.aacrjournals.org/content/canprevres/early/2013/05/08/1940-6207.CAPR-13-0015.full.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003edeveloping lung cancer\u003c/a\u003e, and \u003ca href=\"http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0955286304000403\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ereduce\u003c/a\u003e high cholesterol and blood pressure levels."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/265853.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about garlic.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Ginger"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-ginger.jpg","alt":"Ginger"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/265990.php\" title=\"Ginger: Health benefits and dietary tips\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eGinger\u003c/a\u003e contains a chemical that is used as an ingredient in antacid, laxative, and anti-gas medications."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have found that ginger can potentially prevent \u003ca href=\"http://cancerpreventionresearch.aacrjournals.org/content/4/11/1929.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003einflammation of the colon\u003c/a\u003e, reduce \u003ca href=\"http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1526590009009158\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eexercise-induced muscle pain\u003c/a\u003e, help alleviate \u003ca href=\"https://www.urmc.rochester.edu/news/story/2491/ginger-quells-cancer-patients-nausea-from-chemotherapy.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003enausea caused by chemotherapy\u003c/a\u003e, and reduce the severity of \u003ca href=\"http://www.jpma.org.pk/PdfDownload/3925.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eperiod pains\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/265990.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about ginger.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Grapes"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-grapes.jpg","alt":"Grapes"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"The portability, texture, flavor, and variety of grapes have made them a popular finger food in countries all over the world."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have associated grapes with the prevention of cancer, heart disease, \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/159283.php\" title=\"What to know about high blood pressure\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ehigh blood pressure\u003c/a\u003e, and constipation as well as decreasing the risk of obesity and overall mortality."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/271156.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about grapes.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Grapefruit"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/grapefruit.jpg","alt":"grapefruit"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Grapefruits are low in calories but full of nutrients. They support clear, healthy skin, help to lower the risk of many diseases and conditions and may even help with weight loss as part of an overall healthy and varied diet."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of grapefruit include boosting weight loss, maintaining healthy blood pressure and heart health, and combating free radicals."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/280882.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about grapefruit.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Green Tea"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-green-tea.jpg","alt":"Green tea"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/269538.php\" title=\"Green tea: Health benefits, side effects, and research\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eGreen tea\u003c/a\u003e may well be one of the world's healthiest drinks and contains the highest amount of antioxidants of any tea."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have found that drinking green tea is associated with a reduced \u003ca href=\"http://stroke.ahajournals.org/content/early/2013/03/14/STROKEAHA.111.677500.abstract\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003erisk of stroke\u003c/a\u003e, and may help fight \u003ca href=\"https://www.cuh.nhs.uk/news/cancer-services/uk-scientists-show-super-foods-proven-beat-prostate-cancer\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eprostate cancer\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/269538.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about green tea.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Honey"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-honey.jpg","alt":"Honey"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Honey possesses antiseptic and antibacterial properties."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have found that honey can potentially help prevent \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"BMJ\" rationale=\"Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.bmj.com/rapid-response/2011/10/28/oesophagus-heartburn-and-honey\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eGERD\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e (gastroesophageal reflux), shorten the duration of \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"BMJ\" rationale=\"Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.bmj.com/content/290/6485/1866.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ebacterial diarrhea\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e, \u003ca href=\"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/14651858.CD005083.pub2/full\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ehelp heal burns\u003c/a\u003e, minimize \u003ca href=\"http://www.karger.com/Article/Abstract/319821\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eseasonal allergies\u003c/a\u003e, and \u003ca href=\"http://www.fasebj.org/content/24/7/2576.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003efight off infections\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/264667.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about honey.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Kale"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-kale.jpg","alt":"Kale"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Kale is a great source of vitamin K, vitamin A, beta-carotene, calcium, and vitamin C."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of kale include: reducing the risk of certain cancers, lowering the risk of \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/184130.php\" title=\"What to know about coronary heart disease\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ecoronary artery disease\u003c/a\u003e, and lowering levels of bad cholesterol."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270435.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about kale.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Kiwifruit"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-kiwi.jpg","alt":"Kiwi"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Kiwis are a nutrient dense food, meaning they are high in nutrients and low in calories. The kiwifruit is higher in vitamin C per ounce than most other fruits."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of eating kiwis include: maintaining healthy skin tone and texture, reducing blood pressure, and preventing heart disease and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/7624.php\" title=\"Everything you need to know about stroke\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003estroke\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/271232.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about kiwifruit.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Mango"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mango.jpg","alt":"Mango"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"The \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275921.php\" title=\"Everything you need to know about mangoes\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003emango\u003c/a\u003e is a member of the drupe family, a type of plant food in which an outer fleshy part surrounds a shell (what we sometimes call a pit) with a seed inside. Olives, dates, and coconuts are also types of drupes."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Many studies have suggested that increasing consumption of plant foods like mangoes decreases the risk of obesity and overall mortality, diabetes, heart disease, and promotes a healthy complexion and hair, increased energy, overall lower weight."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275921.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about mango.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Milk"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-milk-glass.jpg","alt":"Milk"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Dairy products, like milk, are a great dietary source of calcium. Calcium has many functions in the body, but its primary job is the development and maintenance of healthy bones and teeth."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Calcium is also important for blood-clotting and wound-healing, maintaining normal blood pressure, and muscle contractions, including heartbeat."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Milk also provides magnesium, phosphorus, vitamin A, riboflavin, vitamins B-6 and B-12."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of milk include: maintaining bone, blood pressure, and heart health, and providing an increase in \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/161618.php\" title=\"What are the health benefits of vitamin D?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003evitamin D\u003c/a\u003e. Deficiency in vitamin D has been associated with depression, chronic \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/248002.php\" title=\"Fatigue: Why am I so tired and what can I do about it?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003efatigue\u003c/a\u003e, and PMS."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/273451.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about milk.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Milk alternatives"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/coconut-milk.jpg","alt":"Coconut milk"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"There are many reasons you might search for an alternative for dairy, the most common being allergies and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/180120.php\" title=\"Lactose intolerance: What you need to know\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003elactose intolerance\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Some people choose to not consume dairy to follow a vegan diet, which avoids any foods that come from an animal, including milk, cheese, eggs, and honey."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Others may cut dairy out of their diet to avoid hormones and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/10278.php\" title=\"What to know about antibiotics\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eantibiotics\u003c/a\u003e in conventional milk, as an \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/107146.php\" title=\"What you need to know about acne\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eacne\u003c/a\u003e treatment, or when following the popular \"Paleo\" diet."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Soy isoflavones have been shown to be beneficial in preventing heart disease, and at least 10 milligrams per day can decrease \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/37136.php\" title=\"What to know about breast cancer\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ebreast cancer\u003c/a\u003e recurrence by 25 percent. Increased soy consumption may be beneficial for menopausal women."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/273982.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about alternatives to milk.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Mint"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mint.jpg","alt":"Mint"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275944.php\" title=\"What are the benefits of mint?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eMint\u003c/a\u003e, also known as mentha, is actually a genus of around 15-20 types of plants including peppermint and spearmint. Mint oil is often used in toothpaste, gum, candy, and beauty products while the leaves are used either fresh or dried for teas and food."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Mint has one of the highest antioxidant capacities of any food. Mint has possible positive effects on allergies, common cold, \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/163484.php\" title=\"What to know about indigestion or dyspepsia\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eindigestion\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/37063.php\" title=\"What is irritable bowel syndrome (IBS)?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eirritable bowel syndrome\u003c/a\u003e (IBS), and skin."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275944.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about mint.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Mushrooms"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/mushrooms.jpg","alt":"Mushrooms"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Mushrooms, though classified as vegetables in the food world, are not technically plants. They belong to the fungi kingdom and provide several important nutrients."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of mushrooms include helping to inhibit the growth of cancer cells, regulating blood pressure, and improving immune responses to infection."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/278858.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about mushrooms.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Oats"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oats.jpg","alt":"Oats"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Oats contain high levels of a type of fiber known as beta-glucan. Beta-glucan is known to help lower levels of bad cholesterol."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of oats include: reducing the risk of coronary artery disease, lowering the risk of \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/155598.php\" title=\"Colorectal cancer: What you need to know\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ecolorectal cancer\u003c/a\u003e, and lowering blood pressure."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270680.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about oats.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Oily fish"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-mackerel-fish.jpg","alt":"Mackerel fishes"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Oily fish, such as salmon or mackerel, is an excellent source of \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/40253.php\" title=\"Can fish oils and omega-3 oils benefit our health?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eomega-3\u003c/a\u003e oils and lean protein."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Potential health benefits of eating oily fish include: \u003ca href=\"http://ajpregu.physiology.org/content/304/7/R523.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003epreventing cardiovascular disease\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"http://ard.bmj.com/content/73/11/1949.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ereducing the risk of rheumatoid arthritis\u003c/a\u003e, boosting infant sensory, cognitive, and \u003ca href=\"http://ajcn.nutrition.org/content/93/5/1025.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003emotor development\u003c/a\u003e, \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"PloS One\" rationale=\"Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0046832\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eimproving memory\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e, \u003ca href=\"http://iovs.arvojournals.org/article.aspx?articleid=2188773\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eprotecting vision\u003c/a\u003e, and preventing \u003ca href=\"https://academic.oup.com/carcin/article-abstract/34/12/2716/2464040\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eoral and skin cancers\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/9978.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about oily fish.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Olive oil"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-olive-oil.jpg","alt":"olive-oil"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"People who regularly consume olive oil are at a lower risk of developing cardiovascular diseases, including \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/150109.php\" title=\"Everything you need to know about hypertension\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ehypertension\u003c/a\u003e (high blood pressure), stroke, and \u003ca href=\"http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1043661807000333\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ehyperlipidemia\u003c/a\u003e (high blood cholesterol and triglyceride levels)."},{"tagName":"p","source":"In addition, olive oil intake may help treat inflammation, endothelial dysfunction (problems with the inner linings of blood vessels), thrombosis and \u003ca href=\"http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1043661807000333\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ecarbohydrate metabolism\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266258.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about olive oil.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Onions"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/onions.jpg","alt":"Onions"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/276714.php\" title=\"Health benefits and risks of onions\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eOnions\u003c/a\u003e can vary in size, shape, color, and flavor. The most common types are red, yellow, and white onion."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Flavors can vary from sweet and juicy with a mild flavor to sharp, spicy, and pungent, often depending on the season in which they are grown and consumed. An estimated 105 billion pounds of onions are harvested each year worldwide."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The possible health benefits of consuming onions include lowering the risk of several types of cancer, improving mood, and maintaining the health of skin and hair"},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/276714.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about onions.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Oranges"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oranges.jpg","alt":"orange"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"An orange has over 170 different phytochemicals and more than 60 flavonoids, many of which have been shown to have anti-inflammatory properties and strong antioxidant effects."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Oranges also contain thiamin, riboflavin, niacin, vitamin B-6, folate, pantothenic acid, phosphorus, magnesium, manganese, selenium, and copper. Because of their high vitamin C content (over twice the daily need), oranges are associated with boosting the immune system."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/272782.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about oranges.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Oregano"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-oregano.jpg","alt":"oregano"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Oregano is a rich source of vitamin K and dietary antioxidants."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have found that oregano has \u003ca href=\"http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/jf0510079\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eantimicrobial activity\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"http://www.pnas.org/content/105/26/9099.short\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eanti-inflammatory properties\u003c/a\u003e, and components in oregano may help slow down or prevent the progression of disease in patients with \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"PloS One\" rationale=\"Highly respected journal,Expert written journal,Peer reviewed journal\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0068808\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ebreast cancer\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266259.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about oregano.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003cstrong\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Papaya"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/papaya-fruit-cut-in-half-with-seeds-showing.jpg","alt":"Papaya fruit cut in half with seeds showing."},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275517.php\" title=\"What are the health benefits of papaya?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ePapayas\u003c/a\u003e grow in tropical climates and are also known as papaws or pawpaws."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The possible health benefits of consuming papaya include a reduced risk of heart disease, diabetes, cancer, aiding in digestion, improving blood glucose control in people with diabetes, lowering blood pressure, and improving wound healing."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/275517.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about papaya.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Peaches"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/two-peaches.jpg","alt":"Two peaches"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Peaches are a characteristically fuzzy fruit native to northwest China. They are a member of the stone fruit family, meaning that they have one large middle seed, along with cherries, apricots, plums, and nectarines."},{"tagName":"p","source":"One medium peach contains 2 percent or more daily value of vitamins E and K, niacin, folate, iron, choline, potassium, magnesium, phosphorus, manganese, zinc, and copper. They have been shown to ward off obesity-related diseases, such as diabetes, metabolic syndrome, and cardiovascular disease."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/274620.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about peaches.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Peppermint"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-peppermint.jpg","alt":"peppermint"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Peppermint is used as a traditional or folk remedy for several conditions and illnesses because of its calming effects."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of peppermint include: treating the symptoms of \u003ca href=\"http://europepmc.org/abstract/med/23416804\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eirritable bowel syndrome\u003c/a\u003e (IBS), calming skin irritation and itchiness, and preventing the onset of \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/73936.php\" title=\"What is causing this headache?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003eheadaches\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/head.12091/full\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eassociated symptoms\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/265214.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about peppermint.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Pineapple"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/pineapple.jpg","alt":"Pineapple"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Pineapple is a source of important vitamins and minerals such as thiamin, riboflavin, vitamin B-6, folate, pantothenic acid, magnesium, manganese, and potassium. It also contains antioxidants and polyphenols, such as beta-carotene."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Fresh pineapple is the only known source of an enzyme called bromelain, which may help reduce joint pain and the symptoms of arthritis, reduce inflammation, inhibit \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/249141.php\" title=\"What are the different types of tumor?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003etumor\u003c/a\u003e growth, and shorten recovery time following plastic surgery."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/276903.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about pineapple.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Potatoes"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/potatoes.jpg","alt":"Potatoes"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Along with the tomato and eggplant, the potato plant belongs to the nightshade family, of which some species are truly poisonous. Today, potatoes are one of the cheapest universal crops to produce and are available year-round."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The health benefits of consuming potatoes include maintaining bone structure, supporting heart health, reducing chronic inflammation, and preventing constipation."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/280579.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about potatoes.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Pumpkin"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/pumpkins.jpg","alt":"Pumpkins"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/279610.php\" title=\"What are the health benefits of pumpkins?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ePumpkin\u003c/a\u003e is an extremely nutrient dense food, meaning it is chock-full of vitamins and minerals but low in calories. There are many creative ways pumpkin can be incorporated into your diet, including desserts, soups, salads, preserves, and even as a substitute for butter."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of pumpkin including supporting heart health, eye health, promoting fertility, and giving immunity a boost."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/279610.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about pumpkin.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Quinoa"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/white-and-red-quinoa.jpg","alt":"White and red quinoa"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Nutritionally, \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/274745.php\" title=\"Health benefits of quinoa\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003equinoa\u003c/a\u003e is considered a whole grain. Whole grains include the entire intact grain seed without removing any of its parts."},{"tagName":"p","source":"In contrast, when grains are milled or refined like white breads, white rice, and white pasta, they have been processed to create a finer, lighter texture, and are not as nutrient dense. Quinoa is also a great source of protein."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Consuming 2-3 servings of whole grain foods per day can reduce the risk of cardiovascular disease, \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/info/diabetes/type2diabetes.php\" title=\"What is type 2 diabetes?\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003etype 2 diabetes\u003c/a\u003e, high blood pressure, \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/150496.php\" title=\"Everything you need to know about colon cancer\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003ecolon cancer\u003c/a\u003e, and obesity.\u2028 Many studies have shown that as whole grain intake increases, the risk for all five of these lifestyle-related conditions decreases. "},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/274745\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about quinoa.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Rosemary"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-rosemary.jpg","alt":"rosemary"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Rosemary is a rich source of antioxidants and anti-inflammatory compounds."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have found that rosemary may potentially help \u003ca href=\"http://umm.edu/health/medical/altmed/herb/rosemary\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003etreat indigestion\u003c/a\u003e, enhance \u003ca href=\"http://journals.sagepub.com/doi/abs/10.1177/2045125312436573\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ememory and concentration\u003c/a\u003e, provide \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"PubMed Central\" rationale=\"Highly respected database from the National Institutes of Health\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3652539/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eneurological protection\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e, and provide protection against \u003ca href=\"http://iovs.arvojournals.org/article.aspx?articleid=2127627\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003emacular degeneration\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266370.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about rosemary.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Sage"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-sage.jpg","alt":"sage"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Sage is rich in antioxidants (apigenin, diosmetin, and luteolin) and important nutrients, such as vitamin K."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have found that sage may potentially improve memory and information processing among people who have mild \u003ca href=\"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1046/j.1365-2710.2003.00463.x/full\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eAlzheimer's disease\u003c/a\u003e and help lower cholesterol and triglyceride levels in patients with \u003ca href=\"http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0965229913001180\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003etype 2 diabetes\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266480.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about sage.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Spearmint"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-spearmint.jpg","alt":"spearmint"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Spearmint contains high amounts of vitamins, antioxidants, and other vital nutrients."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have found that spearmint may potentially have \u003ca href=\"http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S030881460500885X\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eantioxidant and antifungal\u003c/a\u003e properties, reduce symptoms of nausea and other \u003ca href=\"http://www.ipcbee.com/vol15/10-U00041.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003edigestive problems\u003c/a\u003e, and treat \u003ca href=\"http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/6376599.stm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ehirsutism\u003c/a\u003e (abnormal hair growth)."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266128.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about spearmint.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Spinach"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-spinach.jpg","alt":"Spinach"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Spinach is one of the best sources of dietary magnesium and calcium."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of spinach include: helping manage diabetes, helping preventing cancer, reducing the risk of asthma, lowering the risk of blood pressure, and improving bone health."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/270609.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about spinach.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Strawberries"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-strawberries.jpg","alt":"Strawberries"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Strawberries are one of the most popular, refreshing, and healthy treats on the planet; they contain many vitamins and antioxidants that can be beneficial for your health."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of strawberries include: reducing the risk of heart disease, stroke, cancer, blood pressure, constipation, allergies, diabetes, and depression."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/271285.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about strawberries.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Sweet potatoes"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/sweet-potatoes.jpg","alt":"sweet potatoes"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Sweet potatoes pack a powerful nutritional punch. They have over 400 percent of your daily needs for vitamin A in one medium potato, plus high levels of fiber and potassium."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The potential health benefits of sweet potatoes include a protective role against prostate cancer, promoting fertility, boosting immunity, and supporting vision."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/281438.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about sweet potatoes.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Thyme"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-thyme.jpg","alt":"sprigs of thyme"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Thyme preparations may be more effective than acne prescription creams, \u003ca href=\"http://www.leedsbeckett.ac.uk/news/thyme-for-a-more-natural-cure-to-acne/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eaccording to scientists\u003c/a\u003e at Leeds Metropolitan University in England."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Studies have found that thyme may potentially protect against \u003ca href=\"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11130-013-0368-7\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ehypertension\u003c/a\u003e, help fight off \u003ca href=\"http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/ben/mc/2011/00000007/00000006/art00017\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003efoodborne bacterial infections\u003c/a\u003e, and induce cell death in \u003ca href=\"http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/01635581.2012.719658\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link\"\u003ebreast cancer cells\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266016.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about thyme.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Tofu"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269/269143/tofu.jpg","alt":"Tofu"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Tofu, made from soybean curds, is naturally gluten-free and low calorie, contains no cholesterol, and is an excellent source of protein, iron, and calcium."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The isoflavones (a type of compound called phytoestrogens) in soy foods have been linked to a decreased risk for osteoporosis, while the calcium and magnesium in soy may help to lessen PMS symptoms, regulate blood sugar, and prevent \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/148373.php\" title=\"Everything you need to know about migraines\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003emigraine\u003c/a\u003e headaches."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/278340.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about tofu.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Tomatoes"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/273031-tomatoes.jpg","alt":"tomatoes"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"The tomato has been referred to as a \"functional food,\" a food that goes beyond providing just basic nutrition, additionally preventing chronic disease and delivering other health benefits, due to beneficial phytochemicals such as lycopene."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Tomatoes are a rich source of vitamins A and C and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/219853.php\" title=\"What to know about folic acid\" class=\"keywords content-link\"\u003efolic acid\u003c/a\u003e. Tomatoes contain a wide array of beneficial nutrients and antioxidants, including alpha-lipoic acid, lycopene, choline, folic acid, beta-carotene, and lutein."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The benefits of consuming fruits and vegetables of all kinds, including tomatoes, are infinite. As plant food consumption goes up, the risk of heart disease, diabetes, and cancer goes down."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/273031.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about tomatoes.\u003c/a\u003e"},{"tagName":"hr"},{"tagName":"h2","source":"Watermelon"},{"tagName":"div","type":"tag","widget":{"align":"full","image":{"src":"https://cdn-prod.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/269143-watermelon.jpg","alt":"slices of watermelon"},"widgetFormat":"responsive_image"}},{"tagName":"p","source":"Watermelon contains thiamin, riboflavin, niacin, vitamin B-6, folate, pantothenic acid, magnesium, phosphorus, potassium, zinc, copper, manganese, selenium, choline, lycopene, and betaine. Watermelon is a good source of lycopene."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The possible health benefits of watermelon include asthma prevention, reduction of high blood pressure, regulation of digestion, inflammation reduction, and promotes healthy hair and skin. Watermelon is also one of the best sources lycopene."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/266886.php\" class=\"content-link\"\u003eRead more about watermelon.\u003c/a\u003e"}],"propsFor":{"articleResources":[{"displayLink":"onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1046/j.1365-2710.2003.00463.x/full","link":"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1046/j.1365-2710.2003.00463.x/full","title":"Akhondzadeh, S., Noroozian, M., Mohammadi, M., Ohadinia, S., Jamshidi, A. H., \u0026 Khani, M. (2003). Salvia officinalis extract in the treatment of patients with mild to moderate Alzheimer's disease: a double blind, randomized and placebo‐controlled trial. Journal of Clinical Pharmacy and Therapeutics, 28(1), 53-59"},{"displayLink":"journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0068808","link":"http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0068808","title":"Al Dhaheri, Y., Attoub, S., Arafat, K., AbuQamar, S., Viallet, J., Saleh, A., ... \u0026 Iratni, R. (2013). Anti-metastatic and anti-tumor growth effects of Origanum majorana on highly metastatic human breast cancer cells: inhibition of NFκB signaling and reduction of nitric oxide production. PLoS One. 8(7), e68808"},{"displayLink":"europepmc.org/abstract/med/23416804","link":"http://europepmc.org/abstract/med/23416804","title":"Alam, M. S., Roy, P. K., Miah, A. R., Mollick, S. H., Khan, M. R., Mahmud, M. C., \u0026 Khatun, S. (2013). Efficacy of Peppermint oil in diarrhea predominant IBS-a double blind randomized placebo-controlled study. Mymen